text: There's been a lot of misinformation on how Russia's current account surplus is due to collapsing imports. That's wrong. From Jan to Apr 2022, Russia's trade surplus was $129 bn vs $39 bn from Jan to Apr 2021. Of that $90 bn jump, $82 bn is exports. So it's literally ALL exports. https://t.co/Q4JaaYvESn
